<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_astær"
    xml:lang="os">
    <form type="lemma"><orth>astær</orth></form>
    <sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>подкладка</q>
        </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>lining</q>
        </cit></sense>
    <re><form type="lemma"><orth>fæsonastær</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation"
                xml:lang="ru">
                <q>подкладка на спине (у черкески и пр.)</q>
            </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>lining on the back (for Circassian clothes, etc.)</q>
            </cit></sense></re>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>astar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>āstar</w><gloss><q>подкладка</q></gloss></mentioned>.
        Взаимоотношения персидского и тюркского слов не вполне ясны (см.: <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Horn._Gr."/><biblScope>7</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Hübschmann._PSt."/><biblScope>7</biblScope></bibl>). Нет препятствий
        осетинское слово вместе с персидским возводить к основе %i*star-%i ‘стлать’, сращенной с
        префиксом <ref type="xr" target="#entry_a-"/>; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>āstara-</w><gloss><q>подстилка</q></gloss></mentioned>; см. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_stæryn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_astæryn"/>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>astar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>āstar</w><gloss><q>lining</q></gloss></mentioned>. The
        relationship between Persian and Turkic words is not entirely clear (see: <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Horn._Gr."/><biblScope>7</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Hübschmann._PSt."/><biblScope>7</biblScope></bibl>). There are no
        obstacles to trace back the Ossetian word, together with the Persian one, to %i*star-%i ‘to
        form ', fused with the prefix <ref type="xr" target="#entry_a-"/>; cf. <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>āstara-</w><gloss><q>underlay</q></gloss></mentioned>; see <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_stæryn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_astæryn"/>.</etym>
</entry>
